Error-Exception

Error::Exception is an exception base class to be used when fusing the
functionality of both Error and Exception::Class in order to properly
stringify when uncaught in both straight perl invocations and Test::Unit
contexts.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


Alternatively, to install with Module::Build, you can use the following commands:

    perl Build.PL
    ./Build
    ./Build test
    ./Build install

To run coverage testing, run the following command:

    make testcover

Alternatively, using Module::Build, you can use the following command:

    ./Build testcover

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc Error::Exception

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Error-Exception

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Error-Exception

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Error-Exception

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Error-Exception

